r for resisting.  <br><br>Tequ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uikeya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ikeya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/13/01 5:05:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizardry Rules and Specifications Rough Draft</span><hr size=1> Well you people copy and paste it into word and finish it... It was torture debating to fill in correct information and guessing information. Can you guess what won?<br><br>-Ikeya <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaraton.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Araton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/26/01 2:01:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Al'kabor spells</span><hr size=1> The main point (if it can be called that) of this line of spell is that they have a very large radius of effect. I believe it is 35 ft or yds or what ever as opposed to 15 for pillar spells. All in all they are worthless, don't buy them.<br><br>-Araton <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/2/01 2:49:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://prod.homepage.dk/pics/pers.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Al'kabor spells</span><hr size=1> About Root spells: You receive a mass amount of different Root type spells.<br><br>Level 4: Root<br>Level 20: Enstill<br>Level 39: Immobilize<br>Level 49: Paralyzing Earth<br>Level 58: Fetter<br><br>Many people believe in their own little theory about resists, duration, etc., but the thruth is to be found in the spdat.eff (spell effect file).<br><br>There are certain issues about root spells to be considered:<br><br>* Mana cost<br>* Casting time<br>* Recast delay<br>* Resist check<br>* Duration<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Root</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Resistance Check: Magic + 25<br>Mana Required: 30<br>Spell Duration: 8 ticks (48 seconds)<br>Duration Formula: 2<br>Casting Time: 2.0 seconds<br>Spell Recovery: 2.25 seconds<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Enstill</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Resistance Check: Magic + 25<br>Mana Required: 60<br>Spell Duration: 16 ticks (1.6 minutes)<br>Duration Formula: 2<br>Casting Time: 2.50 seconds<br>Spell Recovery: 2.25 seconds<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Immobilize</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Resistance Check: Magic<br>Mana Required: 80<br>Spell Duration: 10 ticks (60 seconds)<br>Duration Formula: 8<br>Casting Time: 1.75 seconds<br>Spell Recovery: 2.25 seconds<br>Recast Delay: 3.0 seconds<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Paralyzing Earth</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Resistance Check: Magic<br>Mana Required: 100<br>Spell Duration: 30 ticks (3.0 minutes)<br>Duration Formula: 8<br>Casting Time: 2.50 seconds<br>Spell Recovery: 2.25 seconds<br>Recast Delay: 2.50 seconds<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Fetter</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Resistance Check: Magic<br>Mana Required: 75<br>Spell Duration: 30 ticks (3.0 minutes)<br>Duration Formula: 2<br>Casting Time: 1.75 seconds<br>Spell Recovery: 2.25 seconds<br><br>(I'm afraid I don't know what Duration Formula means - maybe someone can explain)<br><br>As you can see, it seems the spell only gets better and better. But you have probably heard your old grey-bearded wizard friend say that Root is still the way to go...well, why?<br><br>* Mainly, mana cost. Whether soloing or groups, you often need to use root for emergencies. 30 Mana is just nothing.....but it escalates, and 100 mana is a lot for the level 49 root.<br><br>* Recast delay. If a mob is pounding on you, you want to root as fast as possible. What happens if it resists? Well, with Root you just cast again. With Immobilize and Paralyzing earth, there is a 2.5-3 second recast delay, which can mean the difference between life and death when struggling to root a mob.<br><br>* Resists. Well, the resist check does decrease....but the question is if it really matters. I don't think so. When soloing or grouping you will often be fighting blue mobs, and when quad-kiting you will be doing VERY low blues. Resists are almost the same on these mobs, and the difference between Magic+25 and just Magic check will be minimal.<br><br>* Duration. It does get a lot better from Root's 48 seconds, but well...some people load up a higher level root spell to 'park' mobs for a long duration, others just root to get ahead of the mob if you're in trouble. Often you won't need the long duration.<br><br>Yups you guessed it, I'm in favour of the level 4 spell Root.<br><br>Be aware that this ends definitely with the level 58 Fetter. Fairly low mana, long duration, short casting time, no recast delay, low resist check. This is what you'll be using at 58, but the road from 1-58 is loooong. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umerloc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merloc</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Site Sorcerer</font></td></tr></table></span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/4/01 9:16:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://faust.ece.ubc.ca/merloc/merlocface2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Al'kabor spells</span><hr size=1> You also have to take into account two other factors...<br><br>1. Channeling - If a mob is beating on you, channeling will help you regain concentration.  Lower level spells channel better.<br><br>2. Level based resistance... It's not in the spdat, but lower level spells are resisted less than higher level spells, I don't remember the level breakdown, but the resistance bonus is noticeable.<br><br>When you take these factors into consideration, &quot;root&quot; is the best spell to use for all levels, in almost all situations (exception: getting out of awareness range of an aggro mob).<br><br>Duration Formula is related to how (often?) checks are made to see if a rooted mob will break root.  I'm not sure if there is any difference when casting a DD on a rooted mob, but there is definitely a difference when the mob is unmolested.<br><br>Merloc <p><CENTER><TABLE BORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" BGCOLOR="#CCCCFF" BORDERCOLORLIGHT="#000000" BORDERCOLORDARK="#000000"><TR><TD><TABLE WIDTH="100%" BORDER="3" CELLSPACING="1" CELLPADDING="0" BGCOLOR="#CCCCFF" BORDERC